Task 4: View Running Services
	-List services in all namespaces
		$ kubectl get services -A
		NAMESPACE     NAME         TYPE        CLUSTER-IP   EXTERNAL-IP   PORT(S)                  AGE
		default       kubernetes   ClusterIP   10.96.0.1    <none>        443/TCP                  18m
		kube-system   kube-dns     ClusterIP   10.96.0.10   <none>        53/UDP,53/TCP,9153/TCP   18m

	-Identify Kubernetes system services
		
	-What is the kubernetes service?	
	akubernetes service provides astable network with ip and DNS name and Load balancing between all pods 
	
Task 5: Apply the YAML Files
	$ kubectl apply -f .
	deployment.apps/backend created
	service/backend created
	deployment.apps/frontend created
	service/frontend created
	
